opposite_reasoning: PhysicalObject provides the strongest and most principled opposition to DigitalData. This leverages the fundamental SUMO distinction between Abstract and Physical entities. DigitalData represents pure information (abstract), while PhysicalObject represents material substance (physical). This opposition: (1) Has maximal semantic distance for Fisher-LDA, (2) Is well-established in both WordNet and SUMO, (3) Captures the essential nature of digital data as non-physical information, (4) Provides clean separation without conceptual overlap. The abstract↔physical distinction is one of the most fundamental in ontology and will create a robust concept axis.
